Matthew Nunes, a Warren High School student, has donated a total of 100 face-shields for the staff at Hannah Caldwell Elementary School!

With donations from many people near and far, Matthew has been digitally printing making face-shields for many people/companies/organizations in need of PPE.

You can find out more information about his business on http://www.njshields.org/

Matthew is pictured here with Ms. Janine Dasilva-RTI Teacher at Hannah Caldwell who picked up the donation.

A HUGE THANK YOU TO MATTHEW! Please check out his site.

post_text:
Union County Residents Can Get Financial Aid and More Support During the Pandemic

Learn About it through a Virtual Workshop Presented by Union Public Library

Union County Residents in need of food, financial assistance, or other support can learn how to get help at a virtual presentation sponsored by Union Public Library on Tuesday, July 7, 2020 from 2 PM ‚Äì 3 PM. Juanita Ayala Vargas, VP of United Way of Greater Union County, and a representative from the Community FoodBank of New Jersey will present with plenty of time for participants to ask questions. The presentation is free and open to all. Sign up at http://bit.ly/UPLlive at least one hour in advance.

Union Public Library is located at 1980 Morris Avenue, Union, NJ 07083, with a Vauxhall Branch located at 123 Hilton Avenue, Vauxhall, NJ 07088. For more information, please contact the Main Library at (908) 851-5450 or visit our website at www.uplnj.org.

post_text:
The student's name is Jon Nicholas Fabillar, grade 11. Advanced Placement Studio Art.

The following acrylic paintings are part of Jon's sustained investigation, in which he depicts the superstitions of different cultures.

His artwork, which he has named "Heaven's Greetings", pertains to the belief that when an insect such as a ladybug or butterfly lands on you, it's a lost loved one greeting you. Jon told me that he felt it was important to create this artwork as a meaningful way of marking the time that we are living through and to honor those who have been lost, and those people who have lost loved ones.

At 10am this rainy morning when the @mtnorganization Inc's Drive-Thru Food Pantry opened at Jefferson School they had already given out over 200 boxes of non-perishable items, fruits & vegetables! Their goal of feeding 500 families was supassed and a total of 570 boxes were given.
On hand assisting was Mayor Delisfort, Committeeman People Jr, Springfield Mayor Capodice, Senator Cryan, and Senator Kean alongside volunteers, students, and local community members.
Special thanks to Yvette and Reggie Anderson for bringing their mission to Union, meeting the needs of those less fortunate, and those that have fallen on hard times due to COVID-19.

On hand assisting was Mayor Delisfort, Committeeman People Jr, Springfield Mayor Capodice, Senator Cryan, and Senator Kean alongside volunteers, students, and local community members.
Special thanks to Yvette and Reggie Anderson for bringing their mission to Union, meeting the needs of those less fortunate, and those that have fallen on hard times due to COVID-19.

This video is from Mrs. Saavedra and Ms. Regal's 3rd Grade class at Hannah Caldwell.

At the end of the year, we usually have a class talent show. This year we had to do it virtually.

Jacob Fair starred in his own video about the garden he has been growing. This video makes us so happy because in class Jacob was our class gardener! He has a greener thumb than most adults that I know. I hope you enjoy these.

Thank you to @mtnorganization for bringing their food pantry to Jefferson Elementary School on Saturday, May 23rd from 10:00 am -11:30 am.

The pantry will be a drive-thru only with no contact. Patrons will drive thru keeping all windows rolled up, popping only their trunks. Volunteers will place a box of food in the trunk and once the trunk is closed cars will be directed out of the parking lot.
Each box will consist of non-perishables, fruit, vegetables, salads, bread, desserts, wraps, and meats enough for a family of 4 for a week.

#vauxhall #community #jeffersonschool @jeffblueknights

The series entitled ‚ÄúMost Requested Tunes‚Äù provides the district‚Äôs music students with remote access to quality instrumental music instruction. Did your little one celebrate their birthday in March or April?

Our Union Recreation Department wants to help share some belated birthday wishes for all of our young residents who missed out on having birthday parties with friends, classmates, and family. Send us a picture of how you celebrated your child‚Äôs socially-distanced birthday and we‚Äôll create a slideshow to share on social media. Your child will love seeing their picture in the slideshow and they‚Äôll surely feel special because all of the birthday wishes that the community will share in the comments.

Please send your picture to recreation@uniontownship.com by Thursday, April 30 to be included.

Your child will love seeing their picture in the slideshow and they‚Äôll surely feel special because all of the birthday wishes that the community will share in the comments.

Please send your picture to recreation@uniontownship.com by Thursday, April 30 to be included.

post_text:
Reduce, reuse and recycle.

Take objects around your house and turn them into beautiful artwork.

Have your child make egg carton flowers out of a few simple objects.

1) egg carton (cut into sections of 4)
2) paint
3) scissors
4) glue
5) straws or pipe cleaners
6) paper
7) paintbrush

Layout the supplies for your child. Show them the picture and then let the creativity flow.

Want to share your project? Tag us or send them to goodnews@twpunionschools.org

#WeseeU #WeareproudofU #Ucandoit #UgotTHIS #Umakeusproud #UnionBOE #UnionProud #UnionNJ #uniontownship

#Repost @twpunionnjrec (@get_repost)
„Éª„Éª„Éª
Have you spotted a teddy bear in a window while walking around your neighborhood lately? It's a game that is catching on right now around the country as a way to help encourage kids to get out of the house for some exercise and fresh air. We're calling on all of you in the Township of Union - both residents and businesses - to help us make the Teddy Bear Scavenger Hunt popular here too!

All you need to do is place a teddy bear - big or small, whatever you have - in one of your windows that faces the street. As families are walking around they can search for the hidden teddy bears in their neighborhood. We need to stick together as a community during this difficult time and participating in fun activities like the Teddy Bear Scavenger Hunt are a safe way to connect with your neighbors.

post_text:
Today is "Draw a Picture of a Bird Day" at Hannah Caldwell School. For the past few months, our students have been watching eagles and falcons through live cams. They started off watching the parents with their eggs and wrote observations about how the eaglets and baby animals grow. They learned about their adaptations, life cycles, and habitats. They always looked for live cams of birds all over the world.

Today, the students learned how to draw a blue bird.

The first bird is from Amber St-Dic of Mrs. Saavedra and Ms. Regal's 3rd Grade Class. The second is from Leah Arana of Mrs. Saavedra and Ms. Regal's 3rd Grade Class.

#WeseeU

Township of Union NJ Police Department
April 7 at 11:36 AM ¬∑

In an effort to maintain social distancing, all Township & County Parks and Playgrounds are being closed--effective immediately. The closure is indefinite, but is another measure to try to flatten the curve. We realize that closing the parks is an inconvenience for residents looking to get outdoors, but as more people go to the parks and playgrounds, it is becoming difficult to maintain social distancing. Please try to stay at home except for essential services. This will be a full closure--even walking around or through the park is not allowed.

shared_text:
Township of Union, New Jersey - Government
April 6 at 11:04 AM ¬∑

Join us for a town-wide Easter Egg Coloring Contest from April 6th-12th. Winners will be selected in three categories: Most Creatively Decorated Egg, Most Colorful Dozen, Best Use of Non-Traditional Dyes!

Don't forget to tag us on social media when you submit your pictures so that the Easter Bunny is sure to see your creation! We'll announce winners on Monday, April 13th on Facebook, Instagram, and Twitter. When you submit your pictures don't forget to include some details about your design so we know how you created your egg-cellent masterpiece!
